{"id":26196,"date":"2018-04-07T11:00:54","date_gmt":"2018-04-07T07:00:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=26196"},"modified":"2025-07-08T11:28:43","modified_gmt":"2025-07-08T07:28:43","slug":"ibn-sireen-rulers-your-sins","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/04\/07\/ibn-sireen-rulers-your-sins\/","title":{"rendered":"Ibn Sireen on Tyrants: Your sins worse for you than Ruler\u2019s crimes"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Haytham ibn \u2018Ubayd reported: Ibn Sirin, may Allah be pleased with him, heard a man cursing Al-Hajjaj, so he said, \u201cCalm down, sir! When you arrive in the Hereafter, the smallest sins you committed will be worse for you than the greatest sins committed by Al-Hajjaj. Know that Allah judges with justice! If He takes something away from Al-Hajjaj because of his wrongdoing, He also gives back to Al-Hajjaj because he was wronged, so do not busy yourself with cursing him.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Tawbah li-Ibn Abi\u0304 al-Dunya\u0304 41<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Qushayri commented, \u201cIt is said that a servant will receive his book of deeds on the Day of Resurrection and he will not see any good in it. He will say: Where are my prayers? Where is my fasting? Where are my acts of obedience? It will be said: All of your good deeds have been lost because you were backbiting against people.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Risa\u0304lah al-Qushayri\u0304yah 1\/291<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062b\u064e\u0645\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0645\u0650\u0639\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0633\u0650\u064a\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627 